# Sigma Senior Architect Skill

Design scalable, maintainable systems with informed tech decisions.

## Architecture Decision Framework

### 1. Context Gathering

```markdown
## Context

### Business Requirements
- Primary goal
- Constraints (budget, timeline, team)

### Technical Requirements
- Scale: [users, requests/sec, data volume]
- Availability: [SLA target]
- Latency: [P95 target]

### Team Context
- Size, expertise, constraints
```

### 2. Option Analysis

```markdown
### Option A: [Name]
**Description:** [High-level]

**Pros:**
- [Pro 1]

**Cons:**
- [Con 1]

**Effort:** [S/M/L/XL]
**Risk:** [Risk + mitigation]
```

### 3. Decision Matrix

| Criteria | Weight | Option A | Option B |
|----------|--------|----------|----------|
| Scalability | 25% | X/10 | X/10 |
| Maintainability | 20% | X/10 | X/10 |
| Cost | 15% | X/10 | X/10 |
| Time to Market | 20% | X/10 | X/10 |

## Tech Stack Selection

### Database
| Requirement | Recommended |
|-------------|-------------|
| ACID, relations | PostgreSQL |
| High-throughput writes | Cassandra, ScyllaDB |
| Simple key-value | Redis, DynamoDB |
| Search | Elasticsearch, Meilisearch |

### Frontend
| Requirement | Recommended |
|-------------|-------------|
| SSR/SEO | Next.js, Nuxt |
| SPA | React, Vue |
| Mobile + Web | React Native + React |

## Scalability Checklist

- [ ] Stateless services
- [ ] Database connection pooling
- [ ] Caching strategy defined
- [ ] CDN for static assets
- [ ] Circuit breakers
- [ ] Health checks
